@startuml
' @id(SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @id(SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK)
'
' Objective-side runtime flow of the standalone /mdd-deploy utility
' skill. Guidance-only: it writes artifacts and a runbook then STOPS;
' it never executes a deployment command.
'
' CHANGE (cycle 0016): two adaptive gates and a generalized landmine
' pause are inserted BEFORE artifacts are written:
'   - deployment-purpose confirmation (dev/staging/prod) gates every
'     purpose-driven default; no silent default.
'   - an access-completeness pass over every secured store checks that
'     both a READER and a WRITER are named, each with an identity and a
'     network path the chosen posture admits; holes are SURFACED as
'     blocking questions, never shipped as a complete-looking diagram.
' Both gates SURFACE options for the operator; they never bake in an
' answer. The landmine pause now triggers on ANY choice whose
' correctness depends on a fact not grounded in the inputs read.
'
' @desc(SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE, "How /mdd-deploy turns a one-line description into deployment guidance: validate target=azure-container-apps, read MDD models + the target repo read-only, STOP for a blocking clarification on ambiguity OR a GENERALIZED go-live landmine (any choice whose correctness depends on a fact not grounded in the inputs — access-path + purpose axes, not just app-config), CONFIRM the IaC dialect AND the deployment purpose (dev/staging/prod; no silent default) before writing anything, run an ACCESS-COMPLETENESS pass over every secured store (named reader + writer, each with an identity and an admitted network path; surface holes as blocking questions), then write the deployment diagram, generate secure-by-default IaC in the confirmed dialect sized/postured for the confirmed purpose (surfaced, not assumed), write the STOP-gated runbook, and report — executing nothing.")
' @desc(SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT, "How /mdd-render rasterizes .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml to its deterministic .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg mirror so the deployment diagram is inspectable like every other diagram. Additive, non-gating.")
title /mdd-deploy guidance and inspection (objective)

actor "Operator" as Op
participant "/mdd-deploy\n(utility skill)" as Dep
participant ".mdd/models/\ncomponents + use-cases" as Models
participant "../atlas-ate-server\n(target repo, read-only)" as Target
database ".mdd/deploy/\nazure-container-apps/" as Store
participant "../atlas-ate-server/\ninfra/ (generated IaC)" as Infra
participant "/mdd-render" as Render
database ".mdd/rendered/deploy/" as Rendered

== SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE ==
Op -> Dep : /mdd-deploy <deployment description>
alt target != azure-container-apps
  Dep --> Op : not yet supported (v1 = azure-container-apps only); stop
else target == azure-container-apps
  Dep -> Models : read components + use-cases (the "what")
  Dep -> Target : read README, Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml,\n.env.example, src (READ-ONLY)
  opt ambiguity OR a GENERALIZED landmine — any choice whose correctness\ndepends on a fact NOT grounded in the inputs (access-path / purpose / app-config)
    Dep -> Op : BLOCKING clarification (same discipline as /mdd-cycle);\nSURFACE the gap, never bury it as a runbook STOP note
    Op --> Dep : decision
  end

  group MANDATORY dialect confirmation — BEFORE any artifact (USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT)
    Dep -> Dep : resolve requested IaC dialect (Bicep | Terraform) — exactly one
    Dep -> Op : BLOCKING confirm: "generate <dialect> IaC?"\n(unspecified/unconfirmed -> STOP, write nothing)
    Op --> Dep : confirmed dialect
  end

  group MANDATORY deployment-purpose confirmation — BEFORE purpose-driven defaults (USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE)
    Dep -> Dep : resolve deployment purpose (dev | staging | prod)\n— NO silent default; never assume prod- or dev-grade
    Dep -> Op : BLOCKING confirm purpose + SURFACE purpose-appropriate\noptions (DB tier/redundancy, recommended doorway)
    Op --> Dep : confirmed purpose + choices
    note right of Dep
      Purpose RECOMMENDS the sizing/posture; the operator
      confirms. Secure-by-default is preserved — the vault
      stays most-restrictive; any relaxation is explicit.
      OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-PURPOSE / -SURFACE-NOT-DECIDE.
    end note
  end

  group ACCESS-COMPLETENESS pass — BEFORE any artifact (USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK)
    loop each secured store (Key Vault, DB, ACR, remote state)
      Dep -> Dep : name READER + WRITER; each needs an identity\nand a network path the chosen posture ADMITS
      opt read-but-never-written, OR a writer with no admitted path
        Dep -> Op : BLOCKING: SURFACE the hole + connectivity options\n(allowlist / in-VNet / tunnel), framed by purpose
        Op --> Dep : choice (never auto-decided by the skill)
      end
    end
    note right of Dep
      The diagram is not "done" until every secured store has
      BOTH a reader and a writer with an admitted path. A
      complete-looking diagram with a missing write path is
      exactly the failure this gate prevents.
      OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-ACCESS-COMPLETE / -SURFACE-NOT-DECIDE.
    end note
  end

  Dep -> Store : write diagram.puml (UML deployment diagram; shows BOTH the\nruntime read path AND the provisioning write path; doc-only stereotypes)
  alt confirmed dialect == Bicep
    Dep -> Infra : generate SECURE-BY-DEFAULT infra/main.bicep (+ modules)
  else confirmed dialect == Terraform
    Dep -> Infra : generate SECURE-BY-DEFAULT infra/main.tf (+ modules):\nazurerm provider + remote state backend
  end
  note right of Infra
    FULL PARITY regardless of dialect: Container Apps, ACR,
    Azure DB for PostgreSQL (TLS; tier set by the confirmed
    purpose), Key Vault (Deny + bypass=AzureServices when
    peers private) + BOTH role grants (reader Secrets User,
    writer Secrets Officer), secret refs, ingress 8080,
    pre-traffic migration job. Hardening that creates a new
    requirement (e.g. a locked vault) surfaces the doorway,
    never bakes one in.
  end note
  Dep -> Store : write runbook.md (numbered steps; exact command, location,\nenv/secret; STOP before every state-changing or go-live step)
  note right of Dep
    Enforces every atlas-ate-server invariant identically for
    either dialect. Caveat: migrations-before-traffic stays
    procedural (documented v1 tradeoff, not auto-changed).
  end note
  Dep --> Op : report written files; review the diagram\nand run the runbook yourself. Executes NOTHING.
end

== SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT ==
Op -> Render : /mdd-render
Render -> Store : read .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml
Render -> Rendered : write .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg\n(deterministic mirror; additive, non-gating)
Render --> Op : rendered SVG list

note over Store
  .mdd/deploy/ is an inspection artifact only.
  /mdd-validate, /mdd-review and the /mdd-cycle
  parity loop never read it.
end note
@enduml
